@node Intro "Introduction"

Introduction
------------

Task Control is a very simple program to change task priorities. Now there
are plenty of other programs out there that will do the same job and have
extra features, but Task Control is designed to do a very specific job,
but do it very easily.

In the past when I wanted to change the priority of a task, it would
involve loading up a program to do this. Now most programs that do this
have a farily long winded procedure and in the time it took to make the
change, I might just as well have left it there in the first place.

So Task Control was born. It can be exclusively controlled from the
keyboard, so I can change task priorities in a matter of seconds.

@endnode

